#!
#! remote.in:  an example command file for linklint.
#! This file will cause Linklint to recheck all remote links found
#! on your site assuming you did a site check with "-doc linkdoc".
#!
#! usage: linklint @remote.in
#! 
#! Note: this will cause an error if "linkdoc/remoteX.txt" does not exist.

#---- use the same doc directory

-doc linkdoc

#---- read in all the remote http links and their cross-references
#---- note: "@@" defaults to linkdoc/remoteX.txt

@@

#---- use the -netmod flag to get modified status of remote links

#-netmod

#---- use the -netset flag to get and update modified status

-netset